items.checkin_comment: One of the last beers from Australia. I was expecting something heavy and sweet, but this is actually more on the semi-sweet cocoa end, even a bit of blackened malt and hop bitterness. Caramel is subtle and banana even moreso, within the spice layers.

items.badge_description: What happens when you take two or more amazing breweries, throw them into the tank and let them ferment together? An amazing collaboration beer, that’s what! Cheers to working together to create the perfect flavor. That's 380 different beers that have been brewed as a collaboration.  Try 5 more for Level 77!

Marshmallow, chocolate, apple pie! Cakes and cookies catch my eye. Churn that butter, twist and shout. Put it in a pastry stout! That’s 165 different beers with the style of Stout - Pastry, Stout - Imperial / Double Pastry, or Sour - Smoothie / Pastry. Check-in to 5 more to get to Level 34.

items.checkin_comment:
BANANA!! 
Ho-ly Shiiit!
This absolutely epic brew is one of the best beers I have ever tasted. 
Incredible banana and chocolate flavour and just lasts and lasts. Dark and sweet, this is just divine.
